// Adversarial: FlashStep teleports the breaker to the bolt's current position when the
// dash action fires. Chaos 0.9 action probability is the highest available, triggering
// dash events at near every frame — this maximises teleport events before the breaker
// physics has finished settling from the previous teleport. The adversarial risk: if
// FlashStep reads the bolt position before it has been updated this frame (read-before-write
// ordering hazard), the breaker teleports to a stale position and BreakerInBounds catches
// the out-of-bounds result. If the teleport lands the breaker outside the playfield edge
// (bolt was near-wall and the FlashStep destination calculation doesn't clamp), BreakerInBounds
// fires. BoltInBounds catches any reactive physics correction to the bolt triggered by the
// breaker teleport landing on top of it. NoNaN guards against NaN propagation from a
// teleport target computed from a mid-frame bolt position during physics integration.
(
    breaker: "Aegis",
    layout: "Scatter",
    input: Chaos((action_prob: 0.9)),
    max_frames: 5000,
    disallowed_failures: [BoltInBounds, BreakerCountReasonable, BreakerInBounds, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 6029,
    chip_selections: ["FlashStep"],
)
